s647: Xiang Ji established former Qi King Tian Jia as Qi king.
s668: Second. Tian Rong's younger brother Heng rebelled at Chengyang, attacked Jia, fled to Chu, Chu killed Jia.
s678: Fourteenth. Surrendered to Han, Ang deposed.
s683: Third. Xiang Yu with thirty thousand troops defeated five hundred sixty thousand Han troops.
s689: Qi King Tian Guang beginning. Guang was Rong's son, established by Heng.
s692: Fourth month. King invaded Chu to Pengcheng, suffered defeat and fled.
s698: Thirty-third. Followed Han to attack Chu.
s699: Became Henei commandery, attached to Han.
s700: Sixth. Followed Han to attack Chu.
s713: Fifth month. King fled to Xingyang.
s719: Thirty-fourth. Bao returned, rebelled against Han.
